children.subject: I'm in EE C128 now. There is one problem set a week, a pre-lab (individual assignment) and lab (group) most weeks, and 2 midterms/final. The project hasn't been finalized, but it is supposed to applying control systems to a Tello drone. In terms of what we have done, all the assignments take a couple of hours (nothing unbearable). I find the textbook and office hours more helpful than not. I would recommend it so far, especially if you've taken EE 120.

history.content:
Tried to look at some past comments and there isnt that much new material relevant to the question. Can anyone comment on what the workload is like for either of these courses?

For reference I am for sure taking EECS126 and EECS106a and an easy 3 unit breadth. I am contemplating taking CS 176 as well, but could consider swapping with either of these classes, but the problem is I dont really know what their workloads are like to evaluate how much time I can distribute during the semester. I am accustomed to lab courses, as I took EE 192 last semester and have a lot of experience sinking time into chemistry labs. I have read that 118 and 128 were low workload (minus the 128 labs?), but would like more input.
history.subject: Workload of EE 128 and EE118?
